-- Mark--

here are some ideas about describing existing POST containers:

In general, there are millions of them on the Web in the form:

&lt;form action=&quot;http://www.example.org/post-container&quot; method=&quot;POST&quot;&gt;
  &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; name=&quot;foo&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;!-- more input/textarea/select elements here --&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;

Besides using application/x-www-form-urlencoded as the
accepted encoding, all the various input &#39;fields&#39; have to be
communicated to the processing application. As a first shot
I suggest an rf:acceptsField property in the same style as
rf:indexedBy.

So, the above POST container can be described with

&lt;rf:Container xmlns:rf=&quot;http://www.markbaker.ca/2003/rdfforms/&quot;
              xmlns:rdf=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#&quot;
              rdf:about=&quot;http://www.example.org/post-container&quot;&gt;

&lt;rf:acceptedMediaType&gt;application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/rf:acceptedMediaType&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;http://www.example.com/foo&quot;
rf:shortName=&quot;foo&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;!-- others go here --&gt;
&lt;/rf:Container&gt;

To illustrate some of the issues that arise I tried to describe
the &quot;newsletter-order-container&quot; located at

       http://www.oasis-open.org/newsletters/action.php

(The form resides at
  http://www.oasis-open.org/newsletters/subscribe.phtml)


&lt;rf:Container xmlns:rf=&quot;http://www.markbaker.ca/2003/rdfforms/&quot;
              xmlns:rdf=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#&quot;

rdf:about=&quot;http://www.oasis-open.org/newsletters/action.php&quot;&gt;

&lt;rf:acceptedMediaType&gt;application/x-www-form-urlencoded&lt;/rf:acceptedMediaType&gt;

  &lt;!-- These fields are the ones that can propably be &#39;standardized&#39; for
       all newsletter-order-container: --&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;http://www.newsletter.org/name&quot;
rf:shortName=&quot;name&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;http://www.newsletter.org/email&quot;
rf:shortName=&quot;email&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;http://www.newsletter.org/organisation&quot;
rf:shortName=&quot;org&quot;/&gt;

  &lt;!-- These fields are checkboxes that let the user choose what
       newsletters to order, meaning that we have to find a
       way to communicate to the application that these are
       multiple 1/0 &#39;decisions&#39;.  This is propbaly also common
       to all newsletter-order-container --&gt;

  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;oasis&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;cover&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;dailynews&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;xmldev&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;samldev&quot;/&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;ebdev&quot;/&gt;

  &lt;!-- Below we have to &lt;select&gt; elements with various
       options: --&gt;

  &lt;!-- original value/label pairs:

      Corporate Management/Corporate Management (CEO, COO, President,
VP, Director)
      Systems Management/CIO/CTO/IT/IS/Systems Management
      Net Management/Internet/Intranet/Web/E-Commerce Management
      engineering/Engineering Management
      consultant/Consultant
      other/Other
   --&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;JFunction&quot;/&gt;

  &lt;!-- original value/label pairs:

       vendor/Product Vendor
       user/User
       consultant/Consultant
       other/Other
   --&gt;
  &lt;rf:acceptsField rdf:resource=&quot;&quot; rf:shortName=&quot;interest&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/rf:Container&gt;

What needs to be resolved is how to communicate the possible
option values to the application and propably how to make use of
the additional information that the labels provide (e.g. when the
described container is renederd for a human user with a web browser.

